[2]
Date: Mon, 28 Jul 1997 08:46:08 -0400 (EDT)
From: DEH@VAX8.CFSAN.FDA.GOV
This message in is reply to the recent inquiries concerning Cyclospora. The
FDA is well aware of the problems associated with Cyclospora, and is
currently working with the food industry and consumers to address problems
associated with newly emerging foodborne pathogen. The FDA convened a
forum concerning Cyclospora on July 23, 1997, in Washington, DC. General
information, epidemiology, research, and future plans to address the
problems were presented by scientists and physicians from various
government agencies and academia.
Information from this forum can be obtained from the FDA Center for Food
Safety and Applied Nutrition Web Page:
www.cfsan.fda.gov
--
Darcy E. Hanes, Ph.D.
Food and Drug Administration
200 C St., SW
Washington ,DC 20204
301-827-8075
